Dino Melaye, former Kogi West Senator, has criticised President Muhammadu Buhari’s nationwide address over the End SARS protest. Melaye said Buhari’s speech made him speechless. DAILY POST recalls that Buhari spoke on the End SARS protests, violence and government actions. Buhari also warned hoodlums who have hijacked the peaceful protest to desist. Reacting, Melaye, in a tweet via his Twitter handle wrote: “The speech of the president made me speechless. “Mennnnnn I tire oooo. Recommending panadol for cancer is suicidal. SDM.”